# Release Checklist

## 1. Bump the version

Update `package.json`:

```json
"version": "1.1.0"
```

## 2. Commit and push

```bash
git add package.json
git commit -m "chore: bump version to 1.1.0"
git push origin master
```

## 3. Create the release tag

```bash
git tag v1.1.0
git push origin v1.1.0
```

The GitHub Actions release workflow will build and publish:
- `AI-Hub-1.1.0-arm64.dmg`
- `AI-Hub-1.1.0.dmg`

If Apple signing secrets are configured, the release will also be signed and notarized automatically.

## 4. Watch the release workflow

```bash
gh run list --repo axiscoretech/ai-hub
gh run view --repo axiscoretech/ai-hub --log-failed
```

## 5. Download release assets and update Homebrew checksums

```bash
mkdir -p /tmp/release && gh release download v1.1.0 \
  --repo axiscoretech/ai-hub \
  --pattern "*.dmg" \
  --dir /tmp/release

shasum -a 256 /tmp/release/AI-Hub-1.1.0-arm64.dmg
shasum -a 256 /tmp/release/AI-Hub-1.1.0.dmg
```

Update `homebrew/ai-hub.rb` with:
- the new `version`
- the new `sha256` values

Push it to both repositories:

```bash
git add homebrew/ai-hub.rb
git commit -m "chore: update cask to v1.1.0"
git push origin master

cd /tmp && rm -rf homebrew-tap
git clone https://github.com/axiscoretech/homebrew-tap.git
cp /Users/admin/Projects/ai-hub/homebrew/ai-hub.rb /tmp/homebrew-tap/Casks/ai-hub.rb
cd /tmp/homebrew-tap
git add Casks/ai-hub.rb
git commit -m "feat: AI Hub v1.1.0"
git push
```

## 6. Verify signed releases when Apple secrets are enabled

```bash
spctl --assess --type open --context context:primary-signature -v "/Applications/AI Hub.app"
codesign --verify --deep --strict --verbose=2 "/Applications/AI Hub.app"
xcrun stapler validate "/Applications/AI Hub.app"
```

## Required Apple secrets

- `APPLE_SIGNING_CERTIFICATE_P12_BASE64`
- `APPLE_SIGNING_CERTIFICATE_PASSWORD`
- `APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY`
- `APPLE_ID`
- `APPLE_APP_SPECIFIC_PASSWORD`
- `APPLE_TEAM_ID`
